{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QJvX1dgZo2mUHTMgxGjzKk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Phase 0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN fix-1 Review — codex gpt-5.4 verdict\n2\t\n3\tReviewer: `codex --model gpt-5.4 --sandbox read-only`.\n4\tTarget: branch `phase-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z` HEAD `64c5d6e`.\n5\tBaseline: `277fa4c`. Commits under review: `14a4612` (original), `64c5d6e` (fix-1).\n6\tCherry-pick: `83869d6` on `main`.\n7\tReview log: `dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-1-review-20260527T134214Z.log`.\n8\t\n9\tSandbox note: reviewer could not write this file directly. Main thread promoted from log.\n10\t\n11\t## Verdict: BLOCK\n12\t\n13\t### 1. [high] D4 still claims synchronous vec0 repopulation semantics the engine does not have\n14\tRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:245-298`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1945-1947`, `2234-2289`, `2528-2557`, `2834-2854`, `462-476`, `1192-1194`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/rebuild_report.rs:96-108`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/rebuild_vec0.rs:80-98`\n15\t\n16\tThe cited anchors are real, but the memo's description is not. `rebuild_vec0()` calls `run_rebuild(false, RebuildKind::Vec0)`, and `rebuild_shadow_state()` only truncates vec0 state and resets the projection cursor; the repo's own test locks this in with `rows_rebuilt == 0`, stating re-derivation is async via the projection scheduler. The actual reprojection path re-runs `embedder.embed(&job.body)` and then reinserts into `vector_default`, so D4's claims that the driver already repopulates synchronously, that readers cannot observe a partial rebuild before open completes, and that the migration \"does not re-run the embedder\" are all contradicted by the current code and tests.\n17\t\n18\t## Addressed\n19\t\n20\t- Prior finding 1 (D3 source_type lock) — FIXED.\n21\t- Prior finding 3 (D6 secondary fixture) — FIXED.\n22\t\n23\t## What passed on inspection\n24\t\n25\t- D3 no longer expands source_type to 7 values.\n26\t- Anchor claims exist: `migrate_with_event_sink` at `lib.rs:1238`, `Engine::rebuild_vec0` at `lib.rs:1945-1947`, `run_rebuild` / `rebuild_shadow_state` at `lib.rs:2234-2289`.\n27\t- `PRAGMA user_version` + `migrate_with_event_sink` is the right schema-version ownership path; actual implementation in `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:218-287`.\n28\t- `DROP TABLE vector_default` + `CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE vector_default ...` same-name shape avoids the vec0 rename limitation.\n29\t\n30\t## Reviewer process notes\n31\t\n32\t- `MEMORY.md` absent from this checkout; used repo-local artifacts.\n33\t- Read-only review on `64c5d6e`.\n34\t\n35\t## Orchestrator triage\n36\t\n37\tDate: 2026-05-27. BLOCK — fix-2 required (no override on BLOCK).\n38\t\n39\tThe actual migration shape needs to be:\n40\t\n41\t1. Schema-version gate via `migrate_with_event_sink` + `PRAGMA user_version` (unchanged from fix-1).\n42\t2. **Stage existing f32 rows synchronously inside the migration transaction** (not via `rebuild_vec0`):\n43\t   - `CREATE TABLE _fathomdb_vector_migration_v0_7_0 (rowid INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, embedding BLOB NOT NULL, kind TEXT NOT NULL)` — a regular SQL staging table.\n44\t   - `INSERT INTO _fathomdb_vector_migration_v0_7_0 (rowid, embedding, kind) SELECT v.rowid, v.embedding, r.kind FROM vector_default v JOIN _fathomdb_vector_rows r ON r.rowid = v.rowid`.\n45\t3. `DROP TABLE vector_default`.\n46\t4. `CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE vector_default USING vec0(embedding float[<dim>], embedding_bin bit[<dim>], source_type TEXT partition key, kind TEXT, created_at INTEGER)`.\n47\t5. Repopulate from staging: iterate Rust-side over staging rows (or use a SQL INSERT … SELECT with a Rust-registered scalar function for kind→source_type, but Rust loop is simpler and 1 M rows is fast). For each row: `INSERT INTO vector_default(rowid, embedding, embedding_bin, source_type, kind, created_at) VALUES(?1, ?2, vec_quantize_binary(?2), ?3, ?4, ?5)` where `source_type` is the Rust-computed coercion of `kind` and `created_at` is the migration timestamp.\n48\t6. `DROP TABLE _fathomdb_vector_migration_v0_7_0`.\n49\t\n50\tThis is **synchronous**, **inside the migration transaction**, **does not re-run the embedder**, and **does not depend on `RebuildKind::Vec0`**. Cost ~64-90 s for 1 M rows (two scans of the existing 3 GB f32 data, no embed work). The handoff §1.1 originally specified exactly this shape (`one-pass INSERT ... SELECT vec_quantize_binary(embedding)`); fix-1 incorrectly pivoted to the async rebuild driver.\n51\t\n52\tFix-2 prompt at `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-2.md`.\n53\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9bc34b42-72f6-4ea4-bdb1-fbe5438de144","uuid":"c94d2cb8-f0e3-45f1-a8c6-00b39c39e5b3","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:45:42.566Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-1-review-20260527T134214Z.md","content":"# Phase 0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN fix-1 Review — codex gpt-5.4 verdict\n\nReviewer: `codex --model gpt-5.4 --sandbox read-only`.\nTarget: branch `phase-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z` HEAD `64c5d6e`.\nBaseline: `277fa4c`. Commits under review: `14a4612` (original), `64c5d6e` (fix-1).\nCherry-pick: `83869d6` on `main`.\nReview log: `dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-1-review-20260527T134214Z.log`.\n\nSandbox note: reviewer could not write this file directly. Main thread promoted from log.\n\n## Verdict: BLOCK\n\n### 1. [high] D4 still claims synchronous vec0 repopulation semantics the engine does not have\nRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:245-298`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1945-1947`, `2234-2289`, `2528-2557`, `2834-2854`, `462-476`, `1192-1194`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/rebuild_report.rs:96-108`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/rebuild_vec0.rs:80-98`\n\nThe cited anchors are real, but the memo's description is not. `rebuild_vec0()` calls `run_rebuild(false, RebuildKind::Vec0)`, and `rebuild_shadow_state()` only truncates vec0 state and resets the projection cursor; the repo's own test locks this in with `rows_rebuilt == 0`, stating re-derivation is async via the projection scheduler. The actual reprojection path re-runs `embedder.embed(&job.body)` and then reinserts into `vector_default`, so D4's claims that the driver already repopulates synchronously, that readers cannot observe a partial rebuild before open completes, and that the migration \"does not re-run the embedder\" are all contradicted by the current code and tests.\n\n## Addressed\n\n- Prior finding 1 (D3 source_type lock) — FIXED.\n- Prior finding 3 (D6 secondary fixture) — FIXED.\n\n## What passed on inspection\n\n- D3 no longer expands source_type to 7 values.\n- Anchor claims exist: `migrate_with_event_sink` at `lib.rs:1238`, `Engine::rebuild_vec0` at `lib.rs:1945-1947`, `run_rebuild` / `rebuild_shadow_state` at `lib.rs:2234-2289`.\n- `PRAGMA user_version` + `migrate_with_event_sink` is the right schema-version ownership path; actual implementation in `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:218-287`.\n- `DROP TABLE vector_default` + `CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE vector_default ...` same-name shape avoids the vec0 rename limitation.\n\n## Reviewer process notes\n\n- `MEMORY.md` absent from this checkout; used repo-local artifacts.\n- Read-only review on `64c5d6e`.\n\n## Orchestrator triage\n\nDate: 2026-05-27. BLOCK — fix-2 required (no override on BLOCK).\n\nThe actual migration shape needs to be:\n\n1. Schema-version gate via `migrate_with_event_sink` + `PRAGMA user_version` (unchanged from fix-1).\n2. **Stage existing f32 rows synchronously inside the migration transaction** (not via `rebuild_vec0`):\n   - `CREATE TABLE _fathomdb_vector_migration_v0_7_0 (rowid INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, embedding BLOB NOT NULL, kind TEXT NOT NULL)` — a regular SQL staging table.\n   - `INSERT INTO _fathomdb_vector_migration_v0_7_0 (rowid, embedding, kind) SELECT v.rowid, v.embedding, r.kind FROM vector_default v JOIN _fathomdb_vector_rows r ON r.rowid = v.rowid`.\n3. `DROP TABLE vector_default`.\n4. `CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE vector_default USING vec0(embedding float[<dim>], embedding_bin bit[<dim>], source_type TEXT partition key, kind TEXT, created_at INTEGER)`.\n5. Repopulate from staging: iterate Rust-side over staging rows (or use a SQL INSERT … SELECT with a Rust-registered scalar function for kind→source_type, but Rust loop is simpler and 1 M rows is fast). For each row: `INSERT INTO vector_default(rowid, embedding, embedding_bin, source_type, kind, created_at) VALUES(?1, ?2, vec_quantize_binary(?2), ?3, ?4, ?5)` where `source_type` is the Rust-computed coercion of `kind` and `created_at` is the migration timestamp.\n6. `DROP TABLE _fathomdb_vector_migration_v0_7_0`.\n\nThis is **synchronous**, **inside the migration transaction**, **does not re-run the embedder**, and **does not depend on `RebuildKind::Vec0`**. Cost ~64-90 s for 1 M rows (two scans of the existing 3 GB f32 data, no embed work). The handoff §1.1 originally specified exactly this shape (`one-pass INSERT ... SELECT vec_quantize_binary(embedding)`); fix-1 incorrectly pivoted to the async rebuild driver.\n\nFix-2 prompt at `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-2.md`.\n","numLines":53,"startLine":1,"totalLines":53}}}
